# User MCP inventory

Canonical config: **`~/.claude.json`**. Deep routing: **`~/.claude/skills/mcp-usage-standards/SKILL.md`**.

| Server | Use when | Skip when | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **`context7`** | Library/framework/cli docs lookups | Repo-only reasoning | Prefer over unfocused web |
| **`sequential-thinking`** | Heavy reasoning chains | Tiny edits | |
| **`fetch`** | Static/simple HTTP/HTML | SPA flows, clicks | Lightweight |
| **`memory`** | Durable reusables | Secrets, fluff | Sparingly |
| **`browser-tools-mcp`** | Needed console/network lens | Duplicate playwright run | Pair with judgement |
| **`playwright`** | Browser automation/UI proof | Fetch-only pages | `@playwright/mcp` via npx |
| **`markdownify`** | Convert → markdown ingestion | Out of conversion scope | Respect path env if set |
| **`graphify`** | Graph MCP queries live | **`graph.json` absent** | Use `graphify-runner.sh` CLI |
| **`jcodemunch`** | Code intelligence queries (symbols, references, outlines, blast radius) | File < 50 lines | Configured in `~/.claude.json` |
| **`jdocmunch`** | Docs intelligence — section-level search/read of md/rst/adoc sets (`search_sections`, `get_toc`, `get_section`) | Single tiny config file | Configured in `~/.claude.json` (added 2026-07-11). Index at `~/.doc-index/local/`; SessionStart guard + post-write auto-reindex. One-click reinstall: `~/.claude/scripts/install-jdocmunch.sh` |
| **`figma`** | Figma design file access and component data | No Figma URLs | Configured in `~/.claude.json` |
| **`ast-grep`** | Structural code search via AST patterns (find patterns across files, refactor structurally) | Simple string search (use grep) | Status: active (verified 2026-05-28). `uv run --directory ~/.claude/ast-grep-mcp python main.py` starts cleanly. Use after jcodemunch fails to find structural patterns; pass AST patterns via `mcp__ast_grep__*` tools. |
| **`semgrep`** | Security static analysis, SAST scanning, custom rule enforcement | Non-security code review | Status: active (MCP mode verified 2026-05-28). Binary is at `~/.local/bin/semgrep` (v1.163.0); settings.json updated to use full path. Prefer `semgrep scan --config auto` CLI for Gate 3; MCP mode available for integrated session analysis. |
| **`lean-ctx`** | Context compression — transparently compresses Bash output before Claude sees it | Rarely needed directly | Status: registered in `~/.claude.json` mcpServers 2026-05-28. `lean-ctx mcp` is a valid subcommand (v3.6.0). Hook wiring via `settings.json` is the primary integration path. |
| **`github`** | GitHub API access — PR reads, issue context, CI status, repo metadata | Non-GitHub tasks | Command: `npx -y @modelcontextprotocol/server-github`. Env: `GITHUB_TOKEN` (PAT with `repo`, `read:org`, `read:user` scopes). |

Browser triage: **`fetch`** → **`playwright`** → **`browser-tools-mcp`** (pick one purposeful stack).

Code search triage: **`jcodemunch`** (symbols/refs) → **`ast-grep`** (structural patterns) → **`grep`** (literal strings).

Security triage: **`semgrep`** (SAST rules) → manual review (business logic).

## CLI Tools (not MCP servers)

| Tool | Use when | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **`designlang`** | Extract design tokens/Tailwind/typography from reference URLs | `npx designlang <url>`; 8 commands: extract/grade/battle/remix/pack/theme-swap/brand/pair |
| **`semgrep`** (CLI) | Run `semgrep scan --config auto` for full project security scan | Also available as MCP; CLI for batch scans |
